Detailed Description

template<class TestPage, class TestFixture>
class gaia::testing::PageInstrumentationTestCase< TestPage, TestFixture >

This class provides functional testing of a single page.

The page under test will be created using the system infrastructure (by calling InstrumentationTestCase.launchPage()) and you will then be able to manipulate your Page directly.

Other options supported by this test case include:

  • You can run any test method on the UI thread.
  • You can inject custom Demands into your Page (see setPageDemand(Demand*)).

If you prefer an isolated unit test, see PageUnitTestCase.

Inherits gaia::testing::PageTestCase.

TestPage is extend from gaia::core::Page

TestFixture is extend from gtest/testing/test

Member Function Documentation

template<class TestPage , class TestFixture >
TestPage * gaia::testing::PageInstrumentationTestCase< TestPage, TestFixture >::getPage ( )

Get the Page under test, starting it if necessary.

For each test method invocation, the Page will not actually be created until the first time this method is called.

If you wish to provide custom setup values to your Page, you may call setPageDemand(Demand*) and/or setPageInitialTouchMode(bool) before your first call to getPage(). Calling them after your Page has started will have no effect.

Returns:
the Page under test

template<class TestPage , class TestFixture >
void gaia::testing::PageInstrumentationTestCase< TestPage, TestFixture >::setPageDemand ( Demand *  i) [inline]

Call this method before the first call to getPage to inject a customized Demand into the getPage under test.

If you do not call this, the default Demand will be provided. If you call this after your getPage has been started, it will have no effect.

Parameters:
iThe Demand to start the Page with, or null to reset to the default Demand.

template<class TestPage , class TestFixture >
void gaia::testing::PageInstrumentationTestCase< TestPage, TestFixture >::setPageInitialTouchMode ( bool  initialTouchMode) [inline]

Call this method before the first call to getPage to set the initial touch mode for the Page under test.

If you do not call this, the touch mode will be false. If you call this after your Page has been started, it will have no effect.

Parameters:
initialTouchModetrue if the Page should be placed into "touch mode" when started
